<p>
The integration of North America into the global carbon business arena is=
 ushering in a wealth of new business opportunities for North American an=
d European firms alike.  U.S. firms are quickly making their move to expa=
nd their activities in both North America and around the globe, while Eur=
opeans are setting up shop to do business in the U.S.  The environment fo=
r building new business relationships, taking advantage of new opportunit=
ies, and making deals is undeniably ripe!=20
<p>
Leveraging off our highly successful Finance & Investment Summit series, =
Infocast is launching the new place to be for carbon players with its ina=
ugural Carbon Finance & Investment Summit. This is sure to be the place f=
or players in the carbon market-where carbon players will come year after=
 year to do business and make deals.=20
The Summit will bring together leading investment banks, carbon funds, ca=
rbon companies, private equity funds, hedge funds, project developers, ca=
rbon aggregators, project lenders, energy companies, major corporations, =
clean tech companies and other players to facilitate the building of busi=
ness relationships and to foster new market transactions.
<p>
The Summit will also offer the perfect venue to gain a deep understanding=
 of how these players intend to play in the world markets, the retail mar=
kets, and the project market as well as their plans for technology plays =
and other investment strategies.  They will discuss
<ul>
<li>The type of opportunities they are pursuing
<li>The strategies they are adopting
<li>The type of relationships they are seeking to establish with third pa=
rties
<li>The drivers that will determine which type of deals they are willing =
to make
<li>The factors that will influence the level of their transactions in th=
e coming year
</ul>
The Summit is a highly productive environment where you can successfully =
network and conduct business with carbon players who are leading the way =
forward in developing the carbon markets of the future.
